<TITLE> CA spells out a series of development schemes for the south </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barisal, March 6 (bdnews24.com) - The four-month VGF programme for the Sidr-hit poor families has been extended by two more months. The programme scheduled to end in March will now continue until May, according to a decision taken at a meeting of the council of advisers in Barisal Thursday. The decisions of the meeting were disclosed at a press briefing at the Barisal Circuit House at 7 pm. The meeting formed a committee, comprising representatives of the University Grants Commission and the education ministry to set up an engineering college in Barisal, select a site for Barisal University and start work quickly. The committee will travel to Barisal, discuss with different quarters and present its report, the meeting decided. The other decisions of the meeting included reactivating Barisal airport through STOL services, setting up a 50 megawatt power plant to be run by gas extracted at Bhola, inventing a crop variety suitable for salinity of the land in Barisal area, quick improvement of Barisal-Barguna road, construction of an embankment to save the area from erosion of Paira and Bishkhali rivers in Patuakhali and turning the meteorological office at Kalapara into a modern regional cyclone warning centre. The issue of supplying gas to Barisal from Bhola through the pipeline was also taken up for consideration. Passports will be issued from Madaripur district administration office, according to another decision. Replying to reporters, chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed said: "The government was completely respectful to the law. Law must be allowed to take its own course. Law-enforcement agencies had been directed to take action against all accused." Replying to another question, he said that steps would be taken to increase the number of beds at Barisal Sher-e-Bangla Medical College Hospital and modernise the Barisal river port. During the chief adviser's briefing, his press secretary Syed Fahim Munaim, Barisal deputy commissioner Monzur Ilahi and other senior officials were present. bdnews2
